## Errors & mistakes
- safe_get: my first draft asserted `safe_get({"a": {}}, ["a", "x"], default=0) == 0`. WRONG — it returns None. safe_get only returns `default` when traversal hits a NON-DICT mid-path; a key that's simply absent at the FINAL step bottoms out at `safe_get(None, [], default)` which returns `obj` (None), not default. Fixed to `safe_get({...}, ["a", "x", "c"], default=0) -> 0` (here "x" misses mid-path, leaving ["c"], so obj=None is non-dict and default is returned). The probe had already shown None; caught before committing.
- p_r_f1(8,2,2) gives f1=0.8000000000000002 (float noise) — unusable in a doctest. Used the clean (1,1,1)->(0.5,0.5,0.5) and (0,0,0)->(0,0,0) cases instead.
- Two Edits failed with "File has not been read yet" (object_creation_utils in PR2, classification_scorer here) because I'd only viewed them via Bash `sed`, not the Read tool. The Read tool gate is per-file; always Read before Edit even if you've grepped/sed'd it.

